snippet.textDisplay: I think everything about R Kelly is unfair. They literally have him convicted by word of mouth. What if it turns out that these alleged victims have lied. snippet.textDisplay: Jackson shouldn't even be mentioned in same subject as R Kelly or Weinstein or whatever... Jackson's accusers have been PROVEN to be frauds.  He went to trial in 2005 and came out with 14 counts of NOT GUILTY.  And before folk say oh he paid everyone off (actually the original payment was $23 million and to settle the CIVIL case to proceed to the CRIMINAL one as that's how it was back in early 90s and the law was changed because of it).  Prove it.  Cos you think a black man (that folk like DA Tom Sneddon had to tried to put away) would be able to do pay off and get away with it in America when  powerful white men like Weinstein and Epstein couldn't?  Leaving Neverland has been exposed as a fake with over 60 lies and innocent video footage manipulated to look bad (the originals can all be found online in their original context) by two frauds who leeched off Jackson while he was alive & turned against him when they couldn't make any more off him and have HUGE debts to pay. They've been at this since 2013 shortly after Robson failed to get job as choregrapher on MJOne and can't even keep his then new story straight having amended it in very contradictory ways several times over.  I ain't gonna write much more cos the information is out there if you do even basic research.  Look into Robson, Safechuck (his train station error is a big plot hole) and their creepy director Dan Reed who has said VERY questionable statements himself.   If you want to go play Jackson music, just do it.  There's NOTHING to feel bad about it.  Thousands of people who knew him, spent time with him said he did nothing wrong.  It's just a few money-hungry leeches who made up stuff about him (going back to the 1993 case started by Evan Chandler (about his son Jordan,  watch the superb Square One for easy to understand info about that).   It's time Jackson's name was separated from all these bullcrap accusations.  The man wasn't just a great artist but an amazing humanitarian from all I've read and watched about him.  Proven by facts.  No evidence ever found he did anything wrong. Don't be believing the false articles by Radar Online and Vanity Fair that were exposed as lies.  The man have been odd, eccentric, strange, whatever, but by all accounts he was a good and generous, caring man and should be remembered as such.  Time to leave him and his family including his three children in peace. Plenty REAL monsters to go after.
